source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-2223
Reason: The target compound has multiple functional groups that may affect its melting point. The trifluoromethyl group is highly electronegative and can introduce strong dipole moments leading to substantial increases, around 20-30 degrees. A methyl group is generally thought to provide a modest increase in melting point, probably in the order of 5-10 degrees due to increasing hydrophobic character and molecular weight. Adding these estimations together should give the predicted melting point for the target compound.
